section.section:
The governing body of Frederick County may grant, by law, a property tax credit under this section against the county property tax imposed on:
real property that is owned by Ruritan National;
real property that is owned by any Ruritan club that is affiliated with Ruritan National;
real property that is owned by a nonprofit community or civic association or corporation and is used only for:
a community, civic, educational, or recreational purpose; or
the conservation or preservation of wildlife; or
real property owned by the Audubon Society of Central Maryland, Inc. and appurtenant to the premises of the Audubon Society of Central Maryland, Inc., if the property is used only for:
the maintenance of a natural area for public use;
a sanctuary for wildlife;
the environmental education of the public; or
the general management of wildlife.
